Thanks for downloading gatekeeper for OpenDiamond.  Below you will find
instruction on how to configure your system to run this software.

Description 
===============================================================================
The Gatekeeper is software written in PHP that will allow you to 
define search scopes for you opendiamond applications.  It will 
read the db files created by volcano and allow users to create scopes
based on collections that they have access to.  Gatekeeper will 
allow you to create users and add them to specific collections so 
they may download a scope file that will be used by there application.

Installation of gatekeeper
===============================================================================
Gatekeeper requires a few things to get up and running.

Apache Webserver
PHP
sqlite3 for php

Move the gatekeeper directory into a web accessible directory and you are 
90% finished.

Configuration
===============================================================================
In the gatekeeper directory, you will find a gatekeeper.conf.default file.
Make a copy this file 
# cp gatekeeper.conf.default gatekeeper.conf

Open this file and change the options to match your specific configuation

Create a gatekeeper.acl file and make it writable by the webserver

Create an admin.acl file and add an admin user per line

If using the htpasswd authentication method:
	Modify the .htaccess and correct the path to the .htpasswd file.

If using the WebISO/Pubcookie authentication method:
	Modify the .htaccess to use Pubcookie and add users of the form
    user@DOMAIN.EDU, which is how the Apache Pubcookie module presents them.

FAQ
===============================================================================
Q. I get a Invalid Server Request when I try to load the page.  
A. You need to add Limit in your AllowOverride directive in the http.conf file. 

Q. I never get prompted to enter a password when I load the page.
A. You need to add AuthConfig to the AllowOverride directive in your 
http.conf file
i.e.
AllowOverride AuthConfig Limit




